Welcome!

Hi, I'm Noah. I'm a software developer and student currently pursing a degree in Computer Science. I've had a passion for technology ever since I was a kid and have pursued that passion through my education and work. Here I will showcase a few of my projects and provide a window into my life. If you have any questions or would like to get in touch, feel free to reach out to me.

About Me

  • I live around Washington D.C., USA
  • I'm currently 18 years old.
  • I've used many different languages, but most notably Java, Javascript, C#, Python and SQL.
  • My other passions besides coding include music (I play bass guitar), exploring nature and travelling. As of now, I have been to eight countries.
  • I spent a semester studying in Thessaloniki, Greece.

Projects

Bit Keeper

I made this project in 2023 for a hackathon. It's a simple game made in Unity where you defend your CPU from various "bugs" that attempt to to hijack your system. I would have loved to expand upon this project more, but I only had 36 hours to complete the entire thing.
